  "id": "019d240d-73d4-7383-b53a-2c243b8e1788",
  "content": "# Hooks System Audit — Research Findings (2026-03-25)\n\n## Current State\n\n10 hooks across 5 Claude Code lifecycle events, implemented as 8 bash scripts + 1 inline echo + 1 generated script.\n\n### Critical Problems Found\n\n1. **Silent failure**: 6 of 8 scripts use `exec 2>/dev/null`, completely hiding all errors. If jq fails, session files are missing, or JSONL is malformed — zero visibility.\n\n2. **No telemetry integration**: Hook execution is invisible to corvia's telemetry system (no spans, no metrics, no dashboard traces). This is a blind spot in observability.\n\n3. **Race conditions**: Multiple hooks (record-prompt, record-tool-start, record-tool-end) read/write the same turn counter file non-atomically. Multiple hooks append to the same JSONL without locking.\n\n4. **Shell injection risk**: `corvia-write-reminder.sh` line 9 uses `eval \"$(jq ...)\"` — shell injection vector if tool output contains crafted strings.\n\n5. **Process overhead**: Each tool call spawns 2+ bash processes (PreToolUse + PostToolUse recorders), each forking jq, cat, date. ~8 process forks per tool invocation.\n\n6. **Two disconnected hook systems**: `hooks.rs` generates doc-placement hooks from corvia.toml, but session recording hooks are hand-crafted bash with no generation, no config, no validation.\n\n7. **No hook health monitoring**: Timeouts (5s/10s/30s) are set but failures are invisible. No way to know if hooks are degrading session performance.\n\n### Claude Code Hook Protocol Key Facts\n\n- Hooks CAN be compiled binaries (not just bash scripts)\n- Exit 0 = success, Exit 2 = block action, Exit 1/3+ = non-blocking error\n- JSON on stdin, optional JSON on stdout\n- PreToolUse can return `permissionDecision` and `updatedInput` via stdout JSON\n- Timeout kills the process; for PreToolUse defaults to \"allow\" on timeout\n\n### Ownership Boundary\n\n- **Product (repos/corvia/)**: Hook generation logic (`hooks.rs`), telemetry system, session adapter, knowledge storage\n- **Workspace (.claude/, .corvia/)**: Generated hook scripts, settings.json registration, session JSONL files\n- **Pattern**: Product generates → workspace executes. Same as doc-placement today.",
